    dc:title "Myxosporea (Cnidaria: Myxozoa) infecting the saddled seabream Oblada melanura (L. 1758) (Teleostei: Sparidae) and the painted comber Serranus scriba (L. 1758) (Teleostei: Serranidae) in Tunisia" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.581310> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.581310>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Photomicrographs of Myxodavisia sp. from the gall bladder of Serranus scriba. (A) Mature spores in sutural view presenting the spherical polar capsules (pc) and the straight to slightly curved suture line (sl). (B – D) Fresh smear of mature spores with variable forms. (E) Mature spore showing the sporoplasmic nuclei (sn) and the Capsulogenic nucleus (cn). (F – J) Fresh mature spores in apical view, notice the presence of sutural ridges (sr) in both posterior and anterior ends and the lateral appendages (la). Scale bar = 20 µm in D, 10 µm in A – C, E – J." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/581310/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

